{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EZvs4s6Uy9nWQLBYwXzbuU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Enforce request-validation, permission, service-handoff, and response-contract boundaries in views without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when adding or updating API views.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Execution Checklist\n    23→\n    24→1. Validate input at the view boundary before business logic.\n    25→2. Keep authorization checks explicit and close to entrypoint behavior.\n    26→3. Hand domain writes to a service function (`service_symbol`), not the view.\n    27→4. Return a stable response contract (`response_schema_name`).\n    28→5. Add route and test coverage for the new view path.\n    29→\n    30→## Guardrails\n    31→\n    32→- No domain write logic in view functions.\n    33→- No ad hoc payload parsing that bypasses the request contract.\n    34→- Include both success and access/validation behavior in tests.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e7eeacfc-d12f-4201-816c-706909b48901","uuid":"3d6982e1-1df5-4140-b9b8-cf0a0e0f7a2f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RW7FLjjLsHYnruYepKP8yF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The SKILL.md file is benign - it's a control checklist document with no executable code. Proceeding with the skill's guidance.\n\nPer the view-contract-enforcer skill, here is the enforcement plan for the `entity_summary` view:\n\n**Contract boundaries for `entity_summary` (POST `entities/<int:pk>/summary/`):**\n\n1. **Input validation** — Parse the incoming POST body through `EntitySummaryRequest` at the top of the view, before any business logic. Reject invalid payloads with 400 and do not fall through to the service.\n\n2. **Explicit authorization** — Perform permission checks (object-level access to the entity identified by `pk`) immediately after validation, close to the entrypoint. Do not defer auth into the service.\n\n3. **Service handoff** — Delegate all domain work to `build_entity_summary(pk, validated_request)`. The view function must contain no ORM writes, no domain calculations, and no side effects beyond calling the service.\n\n4. **Stable response contract** — Serialize the service return value through `EntitySummaryResponse` and return it as the HTTP body. Do not hand-roll dict responses that bypass the schema.\n\n5. **Route + test coverage**:\n   - Register the URL as `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")`.\n   - Add `test_entity_summary` hitting `/api/entities/1/summary/` covering (a) success path, (b) validation failure (bad request body → 400), and (c) access/permission failure (→ 403/404).\n\n**Guardrails to verify before merge:**\n- No domain writes inline in `entity_summary`.\n- No `request.data` access that bypasses `EntitySummaryRequest`.\n- Tests assert both success and access/validation behavior, not just the happy path.\n\nLet me know if you want me to apply this to specific files in the codebase."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":712,"cache_read_input_tokens":21710,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":712,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e7eeacfc-d12f-4201-816c-706909b48901","uuid":"f7e18770-1898-4c9b-a9d8-8da3ed60400d"}
